Title : 1883 in Brazil
Text : {{Year in Brazil|1883}}

Events in the year '''1883 in [[Brazil]]'''.
==Incumbents==
*Monarch – Emperor [[Pedro II of Brazil|Pedro II]]
*[[Prime Minister of Brazil#President of the Council of Ministers of the Empire of Brazil|Prime Minister]] – [[João Lustosa da Cunha Paranaguá, Marquis of Paranaguá|Marquis of Paranaguá]] (until 24 May), Lafayette Rodrigues Pereira (from 24 May)

==Events==
*January 21 - Elias Augusto da Silva launches the Reformador, a revision of the Federação Espírita Brasileira. 
*July 24 - [[Campos dos Goytacazes]], in the province of [[Rio de Janeiro]], is the first city  in Brazil to have street lights.
*September 30 - [[Mossoró]], in the province of [[Rio Grande do Norte]], is the first city in Brazil to abolish slavery.<ref>[http://www.senado.gov.br/noticias/jornal/arquivos_jornal/arquivospdf/encarte_abolicao.pdf ''Mossoró se destaca como cidade pioneira''] (página 8) ''Jornal do Senado''. Rio de Janeiro (14 de maio de 1888). Página acessada em 30 de setembro de 2012.</ref>
==Births==
*May 18 - [[Eurico Gaspar Dutra]], minister of war 1936-1945, president 1946-1951
*June 20 - Oliveira Viana, historian and jurist
*October 22 - Abílio Barreto, poet
*November 27 - [[Belfort Duarte]], footballer<ref>{{cite book | first = | last =  | title = Enciclopédia do Futebol Brasileiro Lance Volume 1 | publisher = Aretê Editorial S/A | location = Rio de Janeiro | year = 2001 | page = 35| isbn = 85-88651-01-7}}</ref>
==Deaths==
*April 11 - Arsênio da Silva, photographer
*May 1 - [[Qorpo-Santo]] (real name José Joaquim de Campos Leão), journalist and playwright
